Brundibar is a children&amp;#039;s opera by Jewish Czech composer Hans Krasa with a libretto by Adolf Hoffmeister, originally performed by the children of Theresienstadt concentration camp in occupied Czechoslovakia. The name comes from a Czech colloquialism for a bumblebee.
